@divergencearran I added chat to an app once. Instead of putting a tab that said "Chat" with a üí¨, we made the user learn a new (awesome) gesture. No one ever found it, so no one chatted, and the thing totally flopped.

How to reverse engineer product market fit: 

1. Laser focus on solving a real, specific problem for actual people.

2. Make it obvious; don‚Äôt be clever.

3. Beg users for feedback, and make changes based on that feedback.
